{"word":"ἐκφορά","slug":"ἐκφορά","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐκφορά</b></el> <el>(ἐκφορά, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐκφέρω'><el>ἐκφέρω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a carrying out</i> of a corpse to burial, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>(from <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>) of horses, <i>a running away</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}